Zimbabwe’s Draft Constitution Set to be Submitted to Parliament in October

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 
2011-07-28T08:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/zimbabwe-s-draft-constitution-set-to-be-submitted-to-parliament-in-october.html
Zimbabwe ’s draft Constitition is
scheduled to be submitted to parliament by Oct. 15, said Paul
Mangwana, co-chairman of the constitutional outreach program,
which is writing up the document.  A referendum on the new Constitution should then be held
three months after it’s approved by lawmakers, Mangwana said  at
a conference in Victoria Falls, in northwestern Zimbabwe, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
